abstract: A bloc of eight countries will rename their French-backed currency and France will scrap a contentious requirement for reserve deposits.
snippet: A bloc of eight countries will rename their French-backed currency and France will scrap a contentious requirement for reserve deposits.
lead_paragraph: DAKAR, Senegal — A bloc of West African states took a step away from a French-backed regional currency that dates back to the colonial era, making a significant symbolic break from the past.

abstract: Emails also suggest President Trump first began asking about $250 million in Pentagon aid after a June 19 article in the Washington Examiner.
snippet: Emails also suggest President Trump first began asking about $250 million in Pentagon aid after a June 19 article in the Washington Examiner.
lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — About 90 minutes after President Trump held a controversial telephone call with President Volodymyr Zelensky of Ukraine in July, the White House budget office ordered the Pentagon to suspend all military aid that Congress had allocated to Ukraine, according to emails released by the Pentagon late Friday.

abstract: President Donald Trump on Saturday criticized House of Representatives Speaker Nancy Pelosi for holding off on sending the articles of impeachment against him to the Senate.
snippet: President Donald Trump on Saturday criticized House of Representatives Speaker Nancy Pelosi for holding off on sending the articles of impeachment against him to the Senate.
lead_paragraph: WEST PALM BEACH, Fla. — President Donald Trump on Saturday criticized House of Representatives Speaker Nancy Pelosi for holding off on sending the articles of impeachment against him to the Senate.
headline_main: Trump Slams House's Impeachment Delay as 'So Unfair'
headline_print_headline: Trump Slams House's Impeachment Delay as 'So Unfair'

abstract: Australian Prime Minister Scott Morrison apologized Sunday for taking a family vacation in Hawaii as deadly bushfires raged across several states, destroying homes and claiming the lives of two volunteer firefighters.
snippet: Australian Prime Minister Scott Morrison apologized Sunday for taking a family vacation in Hawaii as deadly bushfires raged across several states, destroying homes and claiming the lives of two volunteer firefighters.
lead_paragraph: SYDNEY — Australian Prime Minister Scott Morrison apologized Sunday for taking a family vacation in Hawaii as deadly bushfires raged across several states, destroying homes and claiming the lives of two volunteer firefighters.
headline_main: Australia's Leader Apologizes for Vacation Amid Wildfires
headline_print_headline: Australia's Leader Apologizes for Vacation Amid Wildfires

abstract: All five parties running in a parliamentary election in Uzbekistan on Sunday back reformist President Shavkat Mirziyoyev, meaning that although the vote will be the freest in decades, it is sure to produce a legislature loyal to him.
snippet: All five parties running in a parliamentary election in Uzbekistan on Sunday back reformist President Shavkat Mirziyoyev, meaning that although the vote will be the freest in decades, it is sure to produce a legislature loyal to him.
lead_paragraph: ALMATY — All five parties running in a parliamentary election in Uzbekistan on Sunday back reformist President Shavkat Mirziyoyev, meaning that although the vote will be the freest in decades, it is sure to produce a legislature loyal to him.
headline_main: More Freedom, but Predictable Outcome: Uzbekistan Votes for New Parliament
headline_print_headline: More Freedom, but Predictable Outcome: Uzbekistan Votes for New Parliament

abstract: With a relentless attack on liberalism, the president returned to his greatest hits: attacks on the “fake news,” environmentalists, liberals and immigrants.
snippet: With a relentless attack on liberalism, the president returned to his greatest hits: attacks on the “fake news,” environmentalists, liberals and immigrants.
lead_paragraph: WEST PALM BEACH, Fla. — President Trump on Saturday largely ignored that he had become the third impeached president in history as he rallied young conservative activists with campaign-style attacks on the “far-left ruling class” at the start of a two-week vacation.

abstract: Governors who issue pardons often do so on their way out of office. But the criticism, and court challenges, can endure.
snippet: Governors who issue pardons often do so on their way out of office. But the criticism, and court challenges, can endure.
lead_paragraph: When a radio host asked Matt Bevin, the former governor of Kentucky, why he had pardoned a man convicted of raping a child, Mr. Bevin’s first response was, “Which one?”

abstract: North Korean leader Kim Jong Un held a meeting of top military officials to discuss boosting the country's military capability, state news agency reported on Sunday amid heightened concern the North may be about to return to confrontation with Washington.
snippet: North Korean leader Kim Jong Un held a meeting of top military officials to discuss boosting the country's military capability, state news agency reported on Sunday amid heightened concern the North may be about to return to confrontation with Was...
lead_paragraph: SEOUL — North Korean leader Kim Jong Un held a meeting of top military officials to discuss boosting the country's military capability, state news agency reported on Sunday amid heightened concern the North may be about to return to confrontation with Washington.
headline_main: North Korean's Kim Holds Military Meeting as Tension Rises Under Looming Deadline
headline_print_headline: North Korean's Kim Holds Military Meeting as Tension Rises Under Looming Deadline

abstract: President Donald Trump complained Saturday about House Speaker Nancy Pelosi's delayed transmission of the articles of impeachment to the Senate, which may delay a trial in the GOP-controlled chamber.
snippet: President Donald Trump complained Saturday about House Speaker Nancy Pelosi's delayed transmission of the articles of impeachment to the Senate, which may delay a trial in the GOP-controlled chamber.
lead_paragraph: WEST PALM BEACH, Fla. — President Donald Trump complained Saturday about House Speaker Nancy Pelosi's delayed transmission of the articles of impeachment to the Senate, which may delay a trial in the GOP-controlled chamber.
headline_main: Trump Slams 'Unfair' Pelosi Delay, Rallies Conservatives
headline_print_headline: Trump Slams 'Unfair' Pelosi Delay, Rallies Conservatives
